Leach Cross (b. 1886) was known as &quot;the fighting dentist.&quot;  He was indeed a dentist, born Louis Wallach in an Orthodox Jewish immigrant family on the Lower East Side.   He won forty-three fights and fought five champions to draws.  See <i> Ellis Island to Ebbets Field:  Sport and the American Jewish Experience </i> by Peter Levine (Oxford University Press 1992).

Carl Morris (1887-1951) was a Kentucky fighter known as &quot;the Original White Hope.&quot;  
